HEADWORD: Absenteeism
<hw>Ab`sen*tee"ism</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The state or
practice of an absentee; esp. the practice of absenting one's self from
the country or district where one's estate is situated.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Absenter</ent>⟦br⟧
